ns1:Tabla_CodigosG_M a ns1:Tabla ;
    rdfs:label "Tabla de funciones G y M modales en CNC"@es ;
    ns1:textoExtracto """\r
·M· Modal function. Those cases indicated with "!", mean the function remains active even after an M02, M30 or a reset and after the CNC is powered off and back on.\r
· D· Default function. Those cases indicated with "?" mean that the default quality of the function depends on the settings of the CNC machine parameters.\r
· V· This function is displayed in the G-code history.\r
| Function | M | D | V | Meaning |\r
| G00 | * | ? | * | Rapid traverse. |\r
| G01 | * | ? | * | Linear interpolation. |\r
| G02 | * |  | * | Clockwise circular (helical) interpolation. |\r
| G03 | * |  | * | Counterclockwise circular (helical) interpolation. |\r
| G04 |  |  | * | Dwell. |\r
| G05 | * | ? | * | Controlled corner rounding (modal). |\r
| G17 | * | ? | * | Main plane formed by the first axis (abscissa), second (ordinate) and third axis (perpendicular) of the channel.\r
""" .

